replies.body:
Give this man medal. Riot pls. Wards are incredibly under-utilized in lower elo gameplay. Players (especially adc mains) that constantly push and over extend get killed over and over again. I as a support notice that for botlane my wards and sweepers are enough to safely protect my adc. However it's not just about warding. Normally I have the river and sides warded and constantly ping my adc or another laner to back off when I spot a gank. This shows lack of map awareness and means that trash who blame me for not helping flame me. There is hardly anything we can do to teach awareness to players unwilling to learn from their mistakes. 

On the other side warding is very important anyway and your argument is perfectly valid and something should be done. 

{{champion:412}}
